inn1.comm: slow one to start of with, short of a length outside off stump, uneven bounce as Smith waits, and waits, and waits and then flays the bat at it and misses
fuller, outside off stump, and this time Smith gets well forward in defence and pushes the ball to cover
good one, movement off the seam as Franklin pitches this one outside off stump and Smith has a drive and a miss
slower one, almost a yorker on off stump, which Smith defends to the on side with a firm 'WAIT' to de Villiers at the other end
back of a length outside off stump, this one comes in a tad but Smith gets behind the line and defends to the onside
back of a length outside off stump, just, and as it comes in Smith turns it in front of mid-on and calls for the quick single, South Africa on their way
wayward delivery to start off with, very, very wide of off stump and moving away further
well bowled, sir! Bond lands this on a sweet length just on off stump and gets it to seam away, and a tentative Smith pokes at it and gets beaten
and again, another fuller delivery, with good away movement, and a leaden-footed Smith drives and connects with air, and wasnt far from off stump either, well bowled
further from off stump, enticing him to drive, he shuffles across and tries to defend  but the ball moves away from him again, interesting stuff this
he oversteps, the ball is full and Smith chases it and gets beaten
gets this one to move off the seam fairly wide of off stump and Smith leaves it be

Bond strikes! Smith gone! This one was again pitched up outside off stump, perhaps a tad slower, Smith's feet go nowhere as he drives at it, the ball spoons up towards cover-point where Oram dives to his right and clings onto it
back of a length on the stumps, Kallis gets behind the line and defends to the on side
good length, moving across him, he stands and lets it be
a tad fuller, and de Villiers comes forward in compact defence, keeping the ball out to cover
great one, moves across him and sucks him into a forward press, and then the ball shaves past the outside edge of the bat
pitched up outside off stump, inviting the square-drive, but de Villiers resists
overpitched just outside off stump, de Villiers drives, and Taylor dives in the covers and saves runs

gone! Franklin slants a few across him and then brings one in, straighter, the ball moved in the air and then came in, de Villiers stood like a duck and got hit low on the front leg in front of about leg stump, and umpire Benson doesnt hesitate to raise the finger
good length outside off stump, moves in, Kallis gets behind the line and defends to point
full outside off stump, gets the ball to swing, and Kallis drives full-blooded and gets beaten as the ball moves in
full again, this time Kallis is to the pitch, driving, but cant beat Vettori moving across from mid-off
full again, this is a much better forward drive, feet moving in all the right ways, and Kallis gets off the mark with a single into the covers
good length outside off stump, he leaves it alone
good length on off stump, no real movement this time, Gibbs comes forward and drives, getting an inside-edge to the on side
good ball, back of a length and leaving Kallis, gets some purchase off the surface too as Kallis goes back and keeps the hands low
fuller outside off stump, Kallis square-drives and Taylor dives at point and saves runs
there's the one that lands full and then comes in, and Kallis manages to get bat onto it, turning it to the on side for a quick single, good movement from Franklin
strays onto leg stump, Gibbs looks to cash in with the flick but gets rapped on the leg, well outside the line of impact, however
now he moves on back outside off stump, in that corridor of uncertainty, and Gibbs thinks about playing it but then holds the bat back at the nth second
overpitched outside off stump, there to be hit maybe, but he swings at it and gets beaten, to end a good over of clinical left-arm seam bowling
fullish outside off stump, Kallis gets over it and jams the bat down on it, defending to backward point with a 'WAIT' back to his partner
back of a length just outside off stump, moves in minimally, Kallis gets across and drops the bat on it, keeping it into the ground
great ball, bending his back into it and landing it back of a length, with more lift, and then gets it to leave Kallis' backfoot defensive
wow! Again Bonds puts his all into this one, banging it in outside off stump, and getting it to leave Kallis as he stands and defends
this one's straighter, still on that back of length spot, Kallis gets well behind it in a hurry and defends to the on side
back of a length outside off stump, Kallis plays at it off the backfoot and gets a thick edge all along the ground in the gap at gulley down to third man for one
good length ball outside off stump, landing and leaving Kallis as he plays and misses again
gets another one to slant past him, just back of a length, and Kallis gets a look at it and drags the bat out of the way
there's a fuller one now, asking him to drive, which he does, and gets beaten again, good bowling from Franklin
a tad slower, perhaps, landing on a good length outside off stump and Kallis leaves it alone for the 'keeper
oh ho ho, now he gets one to kick off the pitch again and leave Kallis as he bends his back and chases it off the back foot, he's really played and missed more than he's connected
slower one, almost a yorker that slants in, Kallis gets bat onto it and drives to cover
good length ball outside off stump, he drives and gets beaten again
back of a length on about leg stump, Gibbs just taps that to midwicket and calls for an easy single to get off the duck
back of a good length on off stump, Kallis gets right behind the ball and defends back to Bond
yowza! Bond bends his back and gets on to just kick off the surface outside off stump, with deviation into Kallis, who jumps up, arches his back, and gets out of harm's way! Test match stuff, this!
good length outside off stump, he leaves it be this time
good length outside off stump, Kallis opens the face of the bat and steers the ball to backward point
begins with a back of a length delivery outside off stump, which the batsman leaves alone with ease
short outside off stump, gets some uneven bounce as it sits up and moves in, Gibbs looks at it with some surprise
good length, gets it closer to off stump, but Gibbs gets the front foot forward and leaves it alone
back of a length outside off stump, pitches and then gets some late movement in, Gibbs has a careful look at it, bending his back to let the ball move in and past him
lands in again in that spot outside off stump, not here nor there, and Gibbs stands up and shoulders arms, uncertaintly blooms in otherwise damp conditions
back of a length again, the slightest bit of movement into Gibbs, who stands and defends to point
back of a good length on off stump, Kallis hops and defends off the backfoot to Bond
good length, moving in and Kallis surprised, the ball does too much and would have missed leg
back of a length on off stump, he defends to the off side
overpitched now, and Gibbs unleashes a firm punch past Vettori at mid-off and picks up four, the first of the innings, in the tenth over
fullish outside off stump, asking him to try the shot again, but he lets it be for McCullum
identical delivery, come on, drive at it, says Bond, but Gibbs is wise to the task and leaves it be
back of a length outside off stump, left alone
back of a length and coming in, he shoulders arms and watches the uneven bounce
overpitched outside off stump, Kallis square-drives and an acrobatic Patel at backward point dives to his right and cuts it off
fuller, moving in, Kallis reacts quickly and jams the bat and pad together in defence
back of a length outside off stump, moves in and stays low, Kallis stands up and gets bat onto it
back of a length again, and Kallis gets behind the line to end off a second consecutive maiden over from Oram
close! Bond lands one on a good length and gets it to move in, the ball stays low and Gibbs pokes at it, getting an edge that lands just before Fleming at slip
back of a length on leg stump, Gibbs clips it to square leg
well bowled, the slow yorker right in the blockhole, which Gibbs does well to dig out
bowls it from wide of the crease, lands it on a backish length and moves it in very sharply, he's hit high on the inner thigh and then reacts well to steal a leg-bye
full delivery, Kallis gets forward and drives, and gets in inside-edge to the leg side
good length outside off stump, moves in, Kallis gets a stride across and shoulders arms
good length on off stump, Gibbs moves across and turns it to Vettori at mid-on who, like McMillan, has shaved off the stuff growing on their chins and cheeks all tournament
good length outside off stump, defended to point
good length outside off stump, slow and moves in, the offcutter, Gibbs thinks about the cut but the balls moves in too much and he has to adjust to keep it out, uneasily
short of a length outside off stump, he watches it into McCullum's gloves
short of a length outside off stump, Gibbs goes for a pull, not timed well, into the ground and he gets a single past short fine leg
snuff's snuff, says Kallis! Oram banged one in on a shortish length, Kallis backed away, used the feet well, and slammed it nicely over extra cover for a big six!
good length outside off stump, defended to cover
fuller on off stump, he gets over it and flicks just wide of McMillan at mid-on
shot! Dragged in short, Kallis swivels on the pull and connects well, but only gets one out to the deep midwicket sweeper, played over it to keep it down
good length slanting across him, he gets forward and drives to cover
back of a length on off stump, Gibbs gets over it and at flicks the wrists over it to place it wide of square-leg
fairly wide of off stump, Kallis thinks about slapping it through the off side but holds back as he sees the ball move away and thats called wide
he backs away to leg, gives him the charge, Franklin then drops it short and wide,  but Kallis manages to sneak that past backward point for two to third man
sweet! Gibbs decides to break free, coming down the track, freeing the arms, and teeing off with a dead-straight six back down the ground!
back of a length on off stump, he waits for it and plays it late, flicking behind square for an easy single
good length outside off stump, Kallis goes forward then back, and drops the hand on it to steer to backward point
backs off to leg stump again, the ball is shortish, and he cuts hard to backward point
back of a length on off, he gets up and turns it towards Vettori at mid-on and calls for the run, Vettori is good to get there but his throw is way off the mark
this one, outside off stump, pitches and sits up and he leaves it be for McCullum to leap up and pouch it
back of a length just outside off stump, played late to third man for one
strays to leg and Gibbs works that off the hips past short fine leg for an easy duece
good length on off stump, this time he gets on top of it and defends to point
back of a length on off stump, Gibbs rolls the wrists and works it towards square-leg for one
makes room for himself, the ball isnt full, and he slaps it into the ground in front of point
fuller on middle and leg, flicked to mid-on for one
back of a length on off stump, worked to mid-on
backs away, picks up the shortish length, and creams it through the covers for four, no stopping that
back of a length on middle and off, real slow stuff, he just gets up and works it to square
again that middle and leg line, easy pickings for the batsman, who works it wide of square-leg
makes room again, and has a full swing of the arms only to get beaten
back of a length on middle and leg, worked through midwicket for two
again worked to midwicket, for one this time
good length on off stump, defended
slower one, good length on middle and leg, he comes over it and defends back to Franklin
oh ho, again he backs away to leg, getting cheeky and looking to late cut that wide of gulley, but misses and McCullum collects
fuller outside off stump, Kallis defends and gets an inside-edge
Flighted on middle and turning in, turned away cautiously to leg
slightly quicker and on off, Gibbs pushes forward tentatively, that could have easily  bounced and bobbed up. Any chance of a short leg?
swept straight to short fine leg. He took that from way outside off. Does he have a plan?
quicker on off, Gibbs pushes it to cover. Not taking too many chances early on
flighted outside off, not much turn then. Gibbs walks across and taps it to the leg side. Seems to be wanting to play it to the vacant leg-side areas. Patel keeping it tight, though
driven down the ground to long-on for an easy single. Good start by Patel
quick one to start with, on middle. Gibbs gets his front foot down the ground and pats it back
Gibbs telegraphs his intentions to come down the track, Vettori spots it and fires it in quick. Gibbs needs to adjust and check his shot to the off side
short and wide this time, cut away for an easy single square
good flight, some dip too. Kallis checks his shot and that could have easily bobbed back to the bowler. Gets to him on the bounce

pulls the trigger but falls flat on his face. Vettori flights one on middle, good loop that time and Kallis down the track and gives himself a bit of room as well. He hasn't got to the pitch of the ball but goes ahead with the wild slash anyway. The attempt was to get it over extra cover but he can't get the timing, it's skied up in the air and Bond completes a well-judged catch at the cover region. That is a big wicket. New Zealand cock-a-hoop
on off and spining away, slip in place but Gibbs defends it carefully to the off side. No chance of any risks now. South Africa in need of stability
flat on middle, Prince stodgy, front foot forward and defends
fine ball again, quick and gets a good loop going, starting from leg and spinning away from the left hander, tapped away to the off side. Playing against the spin, that's a good sign for the bowler
pushed to the leg side carefully
a little shimmy down the ground and drives to mid-on. No run, though. Pressure, pressure
quicker and flatter, back of a length and Prince goes back to push it back down the ground. In-fielders closing in
driven back confidently back to the bowler
tossed up, he comes forward and tentatively defends to the off side
tossed up again, Prince gets forward and defends, the ball rolls to the on side
tossed up, Prince comes out of the box and hoists this over mid-on, not timed well but he picks up two anyway
flat and wide of off stump, he comes forward and then holds back on the shot
flat outside off stump, uses the feet, comes out and flashes the drive, the ball shoots past backward point out towards third man
tossed up, he comes out again and only manages to drive back to Vettori
flat on off stump, Gibbs flicks to square-leg
tossed up outside off stump, Gibbs plants the leg forward and sweeps with the spin, but totally mistimes the shot
quick and flat in the blockhole, Gibbs digs it out to the off side
flighted, good rotations on the ball, Gibbs gets forward and smothers the spin
tossed up on off stump, now he connects better with the sweep to short fine leg
tossed up from around the wicket, on the stumps, Prince defends
flat down leg stump, Gibbs sweeps hard, connects well, and finds the gap as fine leg was up, positive shot
flatter outside off stump, he goes back and punches to cover
flattish outside off stump, Prince comes out and whips it to midwicket
flatter this time, he waits for it and then turns it to mid-on, well played by Prince
tossed up on a length, he plays it late, and with soft hands, to steal one past backward point
tossed up, Prince shuffles across to off, waits on the shot, and then turns it wide of fine leg for an easy single
tossed up, he drives back to Patel
flat on off stump, uses the feet and drives to midwicket
quicker through the air, he gets behind it and defends
quick one, on a length, Prince gets behind it and taps it to the on side
flattish outside off stump, he waits for it and then steers it to point for one
tossed up outside off stump, he waits for it and opens the face, running it down to third man
tossed up on off stump, Gibbs just comes forward and defends
tossed up on middle and off, he gets down to sweep but gets tangled up in the delivery
quicker and flatter on leg stump, worked out to midwicket for a quick single
flat on off stump, Prince flicks to short fine leg
tossed up on middle and leg, Gibbs comes forward and turns it into the gap at midwicket for a lazy single
fired up wide of off stump, Prince opens the face and steers the ball to gulley
flat on off stump, flicked past midwicket for two, well run
tossed up on off stump,  played with soft hands around the corner for one
flatter on off stump, Prince goes back and across and picks up one past short fine leg
tossed up, Gibbs gets onto the front foot and defends to the off side
fired up on off stump, now he sweeps, with the top-edge, in the gap behind square for one
tossed up on off stump, again Prince goes back and across but doesnt time his shot to the on side well
shortish outside off stump, he stands and steers to backward point
flat on middle and leg, Gibbs turns it to short fine leg for a single
flat on off stump, worked straight to square-leg
flat again, now he shimmies down the track, gets to the pitch, and drives hard past Vettori and since mid-on is up he picks up four, well played
tossed up outside off stump, he turns it to the on side but cant find the gap
lands on leg stump and spins sharply down, and the umpire calls wide
flattish on off stump, again he rolls the wrists and places it to square-leg
tossed up outside off stump, Gibbs shuffles across and defends back to Patel
tossed up outside off stump, this time he sweeps hard out to Vettori at deep midwicket
tossed up outside off stump, slightly short, Prince goes back and drives past point for one
flat on off stump, he comes across and flicks, but right to mid-on
outside off stump, on a length, he gets across and pokes that to the off side, McCullum moves quickly and collects
fraction width offered, he plays it late and finds the gap behind square for one to third man
good length on off stump, driven back to the bowler
full down leg stump, he paddles it well past short fine leg and Bond moves quickly on the ropes and cuts it off down there
good length on off stump, he plays it with the movement and gets one past square-leg
fullish outside off stump, he gets down and paddles it, in the air, over backward square-leg, cheeky but safe in the end
good length on off stump, clipped to square-leg
moves onto middle and leg, and Gibbs turns it around the corner with little hassle, but cant beat the man there
flatter trajectory outside off stump, he plays it late, not in control though, and sneaks it past gulley
flat on leg stump, he taps it to square-leg for one
just outside off stump, Gibbs thinks of pulling it hard but misses completely
tossed up on leg stump, swept out to Oram on the ropes
tossed up on middle and off, Prince gets back and works it off the hips for one
tossed up on a length, Gibbs gets back and pulls through midwicket out to the sweeper
down leg stump, Gibbs tries to paddle it, misses, and its called wide, duly
overpitched on off stump, he drives across the line and gets one to mid-on, who's back deep
good length outside off stump, Prince drives back to Styris
back of a length outside off stump, he drives off the back foot to cover
overpitched outside off stump, he times the drive nicely past mid-off for one
good length outside off stump, he plays it late down to third man to bring up a very good 50, his 31st, when his side are in trouble
full on off stump, Prince drives back to Styris
tossed up outside off stump, he sweeps but makes a hash of it
flat on off stump, worked with the spin to midwicket
tossed up on off stump, nicely played out to midwicket for one, and thats the 100 up
quicker, flatter, Prince goes back to manufacture runs on the leg side, the ball bounces and beats everyone
tossed up outside off stump, he goes back and punches it to point
flat on off stump, Prince uses the feet and cant beat midwicket
tossed up on leg stump, Gibbs sweeps fine, collects two
tossed up slower on the stumps, driven down the ground, Vettori moves fast and cuts it off
tossed up, he moves across and works it to square-leg for one
flattish on the stumps, he shuffles and taps it to square-leg for one
quicker ball outside off stump, Prince backs away and opens the face, running it wide of point for one
quicker outside off stump, some room too, Gibbs thinks about cutting but holds off for later
short and wide, driven off the back foot out to deep mid-off
lands it on middle and leg, clipped around the corner for one
good length outside off stump, Prince unfirls that cheeky pick-up scoop around the corner for one, well executed
good length on off stump, opens the face and runs it to backward point
fullish outside off stump, Prince uses the feet well and drives out to deep mid-off for one
wide down leg stump, he goes for the flick and misses out, and umpire Benson signals wides
angled down leg stump again, Gibbs gets forward and paddles it fine, but the signal this time is leg-byes
flattish outside off stump, spins in and Prince steers it to the deep point fielder
fired up on middle and leg, Gibbs eases that off the pads out to Patel at backward square-leg
slow, real slow, outside off stump, Prince thinks about running it fine but mistimes his effort
tossed up outside off stump, Prince comes out and chips that over mid-on, nicely done, the ball lands in no-man's-land and Franklin is slow to retrieve it, giving up a third run
quick and flat, driven back to Vettori
slow, width on offer, Gibbs cuts in the gap at point for one to retain strike
good length outside off stump, played to backward point
strays it down leg and Gibbs scoops it in the gap around the corner for one
back of a length outside off stump, Prince goes back and drives right to cover
half-volley on off stump, Prince just uses the bottom hand to punch it down to long-on for four
good length outside off stump, played to backward point
he's gone! The bowling change works! Gibbs drives at one outside off stump, leaden-footed, and can only look on as the ball clips the bat, the leg, and rolls onto off stump
tossed up outside off stump, played right to point
flat on the legs, clipped out to deep midwicket
tossed up on middle and off, defended back to Vettori
looped up outside leg stump, cant put it away
flat outside off stump, and Boucher sweeps immensely, against the spin, and picks up four through midwicket, top shot!
flatter one outside off stump, he gets back and works it to midwicket for one
back of a length outside off stump, room on offer, Boucher slaps it wide of point for one
back of a length just outside off stump, steered to Taylor at point
back of a length again, this time Prince drives down to long-off for one
nips one in from a length, rapping Boucher high on the thigh, Macca appeals but it was going over the stumps
good length on off stump, driven to mid-on
a tad fuller outside off stump, he plays across the line and the inside-edge gets him a quick single in front of square-leg
yes it is, and he begins with one on the button, back of a length outside off stump, which is defended to cover
fuller this time outside off stump, Boucher drives but cant beat cover
back of a length outside off stump, he gets up and defends to cover
good ball, slower one, 125ks, no room on offer, Boucher can only work it to mid-on
back of a length, nips in sharply and catches Boucher on the high above the knee roll, cant be out, going over the stumps
fuller on the stumps, driven to mid-on
full on leg stump, clipped out to Vettori at long leg for an easy two
short and wide, Boucher pulls and places it past mid-on out to the sweeper, for the single
slower one, fullish on off stump, Prince flicks in the air wide of mid-on for one
full, right up there, Boucher drives hastily to mid-on
gone! McMillan! The ball's full outside off stump, Prince goes for that punch down the ground he so prefers, but gets under it, perhaps beaten by the lack of pace, and holes out to Patel at long-off
good length on middle and leg, Boucher clips through square for one to keep strike
back of a length on off stump, he gets up and works it to the on side
in the blockhole, Pollock drives but cant beat mid-on
slower one, fullish outside off stump, Pollock drives streakily to backward point
again, slow and full, no room to hit, Pollock pushes it to mid-off
back of a length outside off stump, he opens the face and runs it down to third man
back of a length on the stumps, he shuffles and places it to midwicket
yes, he does, and Macca bowls a fullish one outside off stump which Boucher slogs over extra cover and Fulton moves and fields

oh Macca, Macca! Bowls a slow one outside off stump, there to be hit, but Boucher gets under it and ends up slogging straight up in the air down to long-on, where 'Two-meter Peter', as Ian Smith referred to him, chews it up
full and wide, Pollock slashes that to backward point
back of a length, he looks to run it fine but cant beat backward point again
good length outside off stump, gets forward and drives to mid-off
good length again, no room to hit, and Pollock drives back to McMillan
tossed up straight, defended back to Vettori
flatter on middle and off, driven to mid-on, on the circle
too full outside off stump, Hall clips nicely in the gap between square-leg and midwicket an gets three to raise the 150
quick and flat, he looks to cut but gets cramped for room
looped up real slow on leg stump, this time he looks to nudge it fine but misses out
width offered, Hall cuts past backward point for one to third man
back of a length just outside off stump, Pollock gets back and pushes to midwicket
good length outside off stump, he drives nicely out to Oram at sweeper position
slower one on off stump, flicked out to deep midwicket
good length on off stump, quicker one, worked to midwicket again
comes in off a length and he just manages to flash the bat on it, the ball running to backward point
width offered, Pollock rocks back and cuts straight to backward point
he comes down the track to blast that into orbit, Vettori sees it, drops it short, and Pollock has only to defend to point
slow and flat this time, he rocks back and pulls out to deep midwicket
tossed up outside off stump, driven out to the cover sweeper, Franklin, for a well-run two
flat on middle and leg, goes back and nudges it into the gap behind square
quicker outside off stump, he stands and drives to point
flat on off stump, flicked to midwicket. Dot ball. Pressure.
flatter outside off stump, Hall pulls through midwicket for one
full and flat, Pollock dances down the track and clubs it between Patel's hands an and the umpire down the ground
low full toss, Hall comes down and slams it down the ground, clean as a whistle, looks like four but Marshall dives and pulls off a great save, what effort!
tossed up outside off stump, driven to cover

bang, thats six! Tossed up outside off stump, Pollock likes what he sees, plants the front leg down and heaves across the line, sending it flat over deep midwicket for maximum, wonderful bit of hitting
slower one, on a length outside off stump, Hall opens the face of the bat and steers it past point for one
good length, slow ball, Pollock drives neatly into the covers for a single
well done, in the blockhole, quick, Hall can only dig it out back to Bond
full, quick, Hall swings the bat at it and misses all ends up
strays to leg, Hall clips it superbly over backward square leg for four, nice shot
he responds with a well-disguised slower ball, Hall clears the leg to biff it over the  infield, gets under it, the ball spoons up in the air and into Oram's safe hands moving in from long-off
flat outside off stump, Pollock cracks it through the off side for two
full again, Pollock dances out and cant put it away, only jams the bat down on it and gets one towards gulle
full and flat, Peterson flashes the drive out to deep point
full and flat, in the zone, Pollock onl manages to drive back to Patel
full and flat outside off stump, Pollock drives to cover
full outside off stump, Peterson reverse-sweeps and gets one, well played, but a very tidy over from Patel, who's done well at the death
full and wide of off stump, quick, Peterson thinks about the crashing drive but then assumes it will be wide, but its not called
full and wide again, this time Peterson slaps it wide of point and wants two, Pollock isnt keen on the second but Peterson pushes him
slower one, well done, lands outside off stump and Peterson, who's backed away to leg, cant touch it
another slower ball, back of a length on the stumps, Peterson swings across the line, misses, and how close was that to the stumps?
hello, great shot! Full outside off stump, Peterson ambles right outside off and  paddles it excellently around the corner for four!
he responds with a slower one, back of a length outside off stump, Peterson backs away and flashes the bat, and can make contact - a great last over from Bond

inn2.comm: good start from the man, right on a good length outside off stump, Fulton gets up and defends
good length again, drawing Fulton forward in defence, and then he has to hurry to get the bat out of the way as he decides to leave it alone
wide of off stump, getting the ball to move off the seam but he's off key, and a wide is the call
good stuff, late movement off a length outside off stump, to which Fulton shoulders arms
up there in that channell, Fulton comes forward and raises the bat, looking for seam movement away is Pollock
good, tight delivery marginally outside off stump, he gets up and works it to the onside via the inside-edge, and Prince fields
good length, right there for Fulton, who comes forward and defends
short of a length outside leg stump, Fleming nudges it to short fine leg for one
back of a length outside off stump, Fulton stands tall and leaves it be
back of a length on off stump, Fulton hustles to defend back to Ntini
good length outside off stump, Fulton plonks the leg forward and drives nicely, finding the gap in the covers and the ball trickes across the ropes
straighter delivery on off stump, now he shuffles across and works it straight to midwicket
short of a good length outside off stump, Fulton isn't interested in that one
great ball, lands on a sweet length outside off stump, seams and lifts, and beats Fleming's attempted open-faced defence
back of a length, lifts again, Fleming gets over it and keeps it down in front of point
strays to leg stump and Fleming works it to square leg, where Prince muffles the stop and gives up a run
back of a length in that corridor outside off stump, getting Fulton up on his toes in defence
good length again, slower one, stays low as Fulton gets a stride in and shoulders arms
back of a length angling down leg stump, Fulton cant connect with his flick and the ball dies at his feet
good length outside off stump, drawing Fleming forward, and the thick edge all along the ground to third man
back of a good length, from wide of the crease, Fulton stands up on his toes and works it to mid-on
fractionally overpitched, Fulton square-drives and de Villiers stops it with a firm dive at cover-point
still wide of the crease, angled in off a length and Fulton hops to turn it to midwicket
good length this time, much closer to off stump, Fulton comes forward in defence
slower ball on off stump, Fulton stands and defends back to the bowler
strays down leg stump and Fleming clips it in the air down to fine leg on one bounce
moving, back of a length ball outside off stump, Fulton comes across and then shoulders arms
straighter delivery on the stumps, Fulton flicks it down to Ntini moving around from fine leg, he likes them off the legs does Fulton
gets one to move wide of off stump, Fulton isnt interested in ones in that sly corridor
short of a length outside off stump, up on the toes he goes, punching in the gap at  point and taking a single
good length just outside off stump, Fleming gets forward and just defends to cover
back of a length outside off stump, he stands up and punches to cover
back of a length outside off stump, he leaves it be
dragged in semi-short on off stump, or rather just outside, and Fulton swivels into pull, and though not in complete control of the shot, he gets it well over midwicket and the ball reaches the ropes
good length outside off stump, now he stands tall and shoulders arms
good length on off stump, Fulton comes forward and defends to cover
top shot, full on the legs, his bread n butter, and its clipped away for a boundary
straight on the stumps, neatly tucked through midwicket for three, Peterson hauls it in on the ropes
straight on off stump, he shuffles across and works it into midwicket with a quick call for one
better stuff, slower delivery angled across Fleming, who fishes at it, away from the body, and gets beaten
fuller, now Fleming gets on top of it and pushes to cover
bad ball, down leg stump and wide is called as Fleming looks to clip it into the stands
good length ball on off stump, Fleming walks into the shot and can only push to cover
back of a length on off stump, and Fleming, standing well outside his crease, tries to manufacture runs on the leg side but doesnt succeed, lunging over the shot
short of a length outside off stump, Fulton stands tall and drives to de Villiers at cover-point

edged and gone! Ntini persists with his outside-the-off-stump line, Fulton reaches for it and drives loosely, and the regulation thick edge is snapped up well by Hall at second clip to give South Africa the breakthrough
good length outside off stump, he gets forward and drives, not in control, but its in the gap and he's off the mark
back of a length outside off stump, pushed to cover
good length outside off stump, Fulton cant time his shot well at all, Ntini runs in to field
firm stroke, fractionally overpitched and he square-drives, Gibbs gets a hand to it to take some speed off the ball, and Taylor gets just two
strays down leg stump, Fleming tickles it down to fine leg for one
good length outside off stump, Taylor chases it and gets beaten
good length outside off stump, defended into the covers
good length outside off stump, he shoulders arms
fraction wide, and in a flash, Taylor frees the arms and crunches a cut in the gap in front of point for four
better ball, straight on off stump, and Taylor gets behind the line and defends
back of a length on leg stump, worked straight to square leg
back of a length on middle and leg, tucked for room
not a half-volley, but Fleming gets into position and drives excellently down the ground and Peterson's chasing dive is in vain
back of a length outside off stump, steered to third man for one
back of a length, again delivered from wide of the crease, and Taylor defends back to Ntini
whoosh! Ntini tries a shortish delivery, doesnt come off all that well outside off stump, and Taylor tries some sort of pull, missing completely
good length just outside off stump, defended off the front foot to point
drifts down leg stump and Fleming flicks in the air behind square for one
back of a length, seaming in, Taylor is squared up and the edge rolls down to third man
good length outside off stump, Fleming pushes to Hall at point
tries to bounce him, goes awry down leg stump, Fleming opts out of the shot at the last minute
good length outside off stump, Fleming drives in the air but the ball lands in front of the man at mid-off
good length outside off stump, Taylor drives to mid-on
good length outside off stump again, this time he prefers to drive to mid-off
straighter on off stump, pushed down the ground, mid-on moves around and cuts it off
short of a length on leg stump, worked to square leg
good length angling away from him, he comes forward and defends, getting an inside-edge
fraction width offered and he crunches a firm square-cut to point, unable to beat the field
back of a length on off stump, he gets behind the line and defends back to Nel

gone! Nel steams in, fires one in one a good length outside off stump, the ball jags in sharply, catching Taylor on the crease, and without any hesitation umpire Benson flashes up the finger...but oh ho, replays show the ball was going well over the stumps...
quick, back of a length delivery outside off stump, Styris leaves it be
good length on off stump, wristily worked to mid-on
good length, slower one outside off stump, he goes for the drive but it comes out very tame
much fuller this time, on off stump, Styris gets pad and bat together and drives down the ground for two
back of a length just outside off stump, he gets up and drives to mid-off
straighter one this time, off stump, and he flicks through the on side for a couple
back of a length on and around off stump, he stands up and drives into the covers
good ball, angled wide of off stump and then shaping back in as Fleming gets a good stride in and shoulders arms
good length outside off stump, he comes forward and drives, getting an inside-edge to square leg
back of a length outside off stump, pushed in front of point and he calls for the single, but is sent back
good length on the stumps, worked to square leg but not past Prince
good length on the stumps, he drives down the ground, mid-off sprints across and dives, misses, and leaves mid-on to chase it down
bounces him with a good one outside off stump, Styris gets forward and then has to completely get out of the way...stares rom Nel...that was close to his head
back of a length outside off stump, pushed to point
drifts down leg stump, Styris flicks, the ball clips the pad, and a diving Boucher saves runs
back of a length on off stump, Styris pushes off the back foot and Nel fields moving to his right
good length delivery on the stumps, Fleming gets forward and plays it back to the bowler
back of a length outside off stump, he looks to cut but under-edges into the ground instead
good length on middle and leg, tucked away through midwicket to raise the 50 for New Zealand
moves around the stumps, lands one outside off stump, Fleming flashes at it off the back foot and connects with air
identical delivery, except this time Fleming middles the cut and places it in the gap in front of a diving point
good length on middle and leg, turned straight to Smith at midwicket, who only just placed himself there after being at short catching cover
back of a length on the stumps, defended back to Nel
dropped! Nel drags one short, Styris pulls, Prince moves to his left at square leg, cups his hands, but cant hold on
back of a length outside off stump, Fleming stands and runs it to backward point
good length outside off stump, opens the face and runs it down to third man
fuller outside off stump, driven to cover
drifts down leg stump, clipped down to fine leg
width offered, Styris flashes a drive well away from his body, and gets a thick edge that runs down to Pollock at third man
good length outside off stump, Fleming defends to backward point
angling down leg stump, Fleming flicks, ball clips pad, and Boucher dives to save runs
good length delivery on off stump, driven to mid-off who's right back on the circle
good length again, pushed to cover
back of a length outside off stump, he opens the face and runs it straight to Gibbs at backward point
good length on the stumps, pushed to mid-off
back of a length on off stump, Styris gets right behind the line and drives back to Nel
lovely! Short and wide, and he cracks that away with a forceful cut shot, bat coming down in an arc and dispatching the ball to the ropes
full and moving down leg, easily clipped out to Ntini at fine leg
good length outside off stump, Fleming drives and gets gets beaten
back of a length on leg stump, turned around the corner
length ball on off stump, turned in the air but it lands safely in front of midwicket
back of a length outside off stump, his feet go nowhere as he drives at it and luckily for him the inside-edge evades off stump
full on middle and leg, driven to midwicket
moving down leg stump and he turns it down to fine leg
good length just outside off stump, he comes forward and defends to the off side
good length on leg stump, turned off the pads to midwicket
back of a length outside off stump, pushed off the backfoot to Hall at point
bounces him outside off stump, Styris uneasily pulls in the air over midwicket and lands it safely in the gap, picking up one
good length outside off stump, driven to mid-off
angled down leg stump and its called wide by umpire Benson
down leg stump again, Fleming clips it out to Kallis - heck, I'd forgotten about him - down at fine leg
drifts down leg third ball in a row, and now Styris works him for a single wide of square leg...Nel lets out a yelp
good length outside off stump, Fleming comes forward and pushes to point
dropped! Nel gets Fleming to move into pull a short-pitched delivery, outside off stump, get tangled up, get an edge, and looks on as Boucher leaps high,  gets gloves to it, and lets it go behind him
full and moving down leg stump, wide called
good length ball on off stump, pushed back to Hall
now he sends the rank half-volley screaming over covers, with some authority, and raises his 8,000th run in ODIs
good length outside off stump, comes forward and runs it to backward point
slower one on a length outside off stump, he lunges forward and drives to backward point again
overpitched again, down on one knee he goes, driving out to the cover sweeper
good length outside off stump, gets forward and drives to mid-off sweetly
good length delivery outside leg stump, Fleming looks to tickle it fine, but falls over in his shot
good length on middle stump, Fleming gets across and defends back to Kallis
good length ball on middle and off, slower ball, defended again

bangs in a long-hop, Fleming hooks, not in control, but it lands somewhere down near a moving fine leg, where Hall tries some pretty nifty footwork to stop the four but replays show his foot touched the ropes
good length outside off stump, driven to cover
shorter one outside off stump, too close to cut but he does so all the same, failing to time it well
tossed up on off stump, works it from out in front of his pad to square leg
tossed up on off stump, turned to the on side, Peterson runs across and fields
flat on middle and off, picked for a single wide of square leg
tossed up outside off stump, driven into the covers for one, no hassles at all
flat down leg stump, worked right to short fine leg
tossed up, he comes out and turns it straight to midwicket
slower one on a length outside off stump, sucking Styris into a drive and beating him
slower one again on off stump, Styris drives to mid-off
now he steps out, looking to get aggressive, the balls not there to be creamed, he  gets under it, but luckily for him it lands safely over mid-on's head
drifts down leg stump and he helps it along down to fine leg
good length on off stump, Fleming lunges forward and defends, the ball rolls to point
fraction short and wide, Fleming cuts straight to backward point, Gibbs
flat on leg stump, flicked to de Villiers at square leg
tossed up, out comes Styris, driving well over extra cover for four, good shot
tossed up on middle and leg, worked out to cow corner for one
tossed up on off stump, worked across to mid-on for one
looped up outside off stump, pushed to Gibbs at point
thats well outside leg stump
tossed up, Styris drives back in the air well wide of Peterson, who dives full stretch to his left but the ball dies on him, great effort though

dropped! Can you believe it? Short, not there to cut, Fleming goes for it, the ball shoots up in the air to the left of Gibbs at backward point, who catches it totally horizontal, but lets it pop out as he hits the ground
good length delivery outside off stump, Fleming gets forward and lets it go
short and wide again, this time he cuts late and gets one down to third man
slower ball on off stump, turned to mid-on
back of a length on off stump, squares him up, ball scoots to point
back of a length on off stump, defended to the off side
flat on off stump, he waits for it and then pushes into the point region
flat on off stump, Fleming comes down the track and drives to mid-on
tossed up, defended to the on side
looped up, he comes out and drives to cover
flat this time, outside off stump, he drives out to deep extra cover and the 100 comes up
tossed up outside off stump, he comes out and defends, the ball pops up and lands safely
good length outside off stump, he heaves at it and mistimes to mid-on
good length on off stump, worked to Prince at midwicket for one
offers a long-hop, which Fleming pulls with control out to deep square leg
back of a length outside off stump, Styris shuffles across and works it to leg
out he comes, and lofts this nicely down to long-on for four, was up in the air for some time but there was no one down there
strays down leg stump, Fleming nudges it down to fine leg for one
flat, wide, rubbish, and Fleming just flays it through cover and the ball makes the rope's acquaintance
flatter on middle and leg, pushed to mid-on
comes out a touch, Peterson fires it in, Styris pushes to mid-on
uses the feet nicely, getting to the pitch and picking it up off the legs handsomely over mid-on for four
poor stuff, very wide outside leg stump, pressure showing
flat on middle and off, eased down to long-off for one
flat on the legs, Fleming just nudges that square and rushes down the track to complete his 50
and he takes one ball to strike! Its just outside off stump, Fleming stands there and thinks its good enough to cut, but ends up getting a fine edge into Boucher's gloves, a great take!
good length, jags in as McMillan plays at it tamely
good length outside off stump, McMillan gets forward and pushes back towards Pollock
back of a length on middle stump, tapped to the on side
back of a length outside off stump, he gets forward and drives wide of point to open his account
good length bang on the stumps, Styris pushes that to mid-off
good length on middle and off, nudged behind square for a single
back of a length on the stumps, up he goes, punching off the back foot to mid-on, but de Villiers dives and does extremely well

this one nips in off the seam, sharply, striking him high above the knee roll as he was pinned to the crease, a very good shout, looked close but Harper shakes his head...and Hawkeye shows that it was indeed carrying on over the stumps
overpitched outside off stump and he drives into the covers
good length and now he drives to cover
down the legs, wide called, but a nice take from Boucher
full in the zone on leg stump, he looks to flick but gets the bat face on it and the ball scoots to the off side
back of a length outside off stump, he drives to Gibbs at backward fumble, and the fumble allows a run
fuller on middle and off, tickled fine for one more
straighter one this time, and Styris nudges it off the pads for one, easy singles
back of a length around off stump, played back to Pollock
slower, fuller, and its driven back to the bowler
good length outside off stump, again he just drives back to Pollock's left
quick, drifting well down leg stump, Styris stands and tries that nudge around the corner again, gets hit, they ask the question very late, but Harper isnt interested
good length outside off stump, pushed to cover
overpitched, he flashes the square-drive to Gibbs at backward point
on a length, around off and middle, leans forward, steers to point
length-delivery, skidding on after pitching on middle stump line, McMillan leans forward, drives to mid-on
comes in from off stump line, pushed back down the track. For some reason Boucher gets excited, shouts some words of encouragement to the bowler. He is a wicketkeeper. He has to.
back of length, outside off stump, cut to deep point
off cutter, on the middle and leg stump line, attempts to turn it to on side, misses and it thuds into the pad
on the middle and off, punched back to the bowler
And again. The bottom-hand came of the bat handle this time, the bat-face shut and the ball rolled back down the track
fuller, outside off stump, driven towards cover
full, straight, on the middle stump line, tapped back to Pollock
length-delivery, angling down leg side, Styris had backed away and was cramped for the room as the ball darted back in, and it hit the pad and ran down to short third man area
on a length but outside off stump and McMillan bunted it over extra cover. Hit on the up
sliding on the middle and leg, flicked to deep midwicket
Width outside off, carved away to sweeper cover
on the legs, flicked to long leg
on the off stump line, pushed to cover
on the middle stump line, sliding towards middle and leg, glanced off the hips, past square-leg
on the off and middle, pushed to cover
slightly slower, outside off, jabbed away to point
fuller, on the middle and leg, wristed past square-leg
yet another single down to the long on
beaten. In the zone outside off, on a length and it straightened, Styris  pushes inside the line
fuller, outside off, square-driven to left of point where Gibbs dives to make the stop.
beaten again. Slightly short, outside off, he shapes to pull but it doesn't bounce as much and the bat goes over the ball
leans forward, pats a length-delivery to cover, wants a single - must be bored, and retreats
banged in short, outside off stump, pulled past square leg
good length on off stump, just pushed to point
good length on middle and off, driven to mid-on for a quick single
back of a length on the stumps, gets back and drives to mid-on
back of a length outside off stump, steered to backward point where Gibbs misfields
fuller, slower, he plays across the line and works it to midwicket
strays to leg stump and McMillan tucks it around the corner
overpitched, he drives to cover, where Peterson dives and doesnt quite collect it fluently
backs away to leg, the ball is short, and he drives to cover
well bowled, a fine yorker in the blockhole, he does well to dig it out
overpitched, he stands rooted and square-drives in the gap at point for one
back of a length outside off stump, slower one, he plays it late and runs it to Gibbs at backward point
attempted yorker on off stump, well directed, Styris uses the feet well and keeps it out to cover
back of a length outside off stump, sits up a touch, McMillan is surprised by plays it with soft hands to backward point, set off, and is sent back
dragged in short, McMillan doesnt do much, just stands and lobs it up in the air backward of square, and the ball lands between two men, running in
short again outside off stump, Styris looks for the pull but chops into the ground as he swivels
good length outside off stump, he square-drives past point and thats another Styris fifty in this World Cup...ho hum
he backs away to leg, trying some sort of late dab over the 'keeper, but is beaten by the pace and bounce of Ntini
bang, thats four! Makes room to free the arms, and smacks the half-volley between cover and mid-off
tossed up, he just shimmies down the track and chips over mid-off for one
boosh! Tossed up, he steps away to leg, sets himself up, and slogs it off the middle of the bat for a dinger over wide long-on!
quicker one, short too, he dabs it to Gibbs at backward point
tossed up, he drives to cover
tossed up, again he drives to the off
short and wide, he waits for it and cuts in the gap between cover and point to keep strike
short of a good length outside off stump, he opens the face and runs it down to third man for one
moves to leg, Ntini follows him with a yorker outside leg stump, Styris counters that with a firm drive to mid-off
full, he lines up and swings that down to long-on for four
backs away to leg, Ntini chases him with a bouncer, which sails over his left shoulder as he gets down on his haunches, wide is the signal
fullish on middle and leg, Styris chips that down the ground and it lands safely in front of the man down there
now he too makes room to leg and Ntini fires it in full, McMillan defends to the off side
too full drifting down leg stump, and he clips the low full toss out to deep backward square leg
fired in on middle stump, he uses the feet well and drives, inside-out, into the covers
full and flat down leg, he sweeps, misses, and Peterson pleads for the wicket...Harper just shakes his head
full in the blockhole again, Styris uses the feet and drives to cover

gone this time! Styris looks to end this affair in an array of big hits, dances out of his crease, gets under it and ends up hitting it too hard, and Gibbs, with the sun in his eyes, judges it well moving back from mid-off and takes it
flat on middle and leg, he shuffles and works it nicely behind square, softly, and some quick running gets him a brace
similar delivery, and this time he works this between midwicket for another hard-run two
back of a length outside off stump, Oram defends to point
back of a length again, this time he defends with an inside-edge to the on side
good length now, and he gets forward in defence
good length on off stump, driven back to Ntini
fuller on leg stump, and he's off the mark with a deft flick past square leg
back of a length outside off stump, he drives but mistimes it into the ground
tossed up, McMillan leans forward and drives, there's a noise, Boucher fumbles...edge? Ground? I cant tell.
tossed up, this time he tucks it into midwicket for one
short and wide, Oram crunches that off the back foot to cover, where AB de Villiers flings himself around to save runs
another bad ball, but that man de Villiers is a livewire in the covers and robs Oram of runs
tossed up, he drives to de Villiers again
tossed up outside leg stump, down he goes in an attempt to sweep, but fails
pitches it on leg stump, and Oram tucks it past square leg, a misfield in the deep allows the second
back of a length outside off stump, steered to backward point
back of a length on the stumps, clipped to Peterson at mid-on, who has a shy at the nonstriker's end and McMillan has to dive to get back in
bounces the big man, who loses sight of it and awkwardly gets out of the way
short of a length outside off stump, caressed past point for one
good length on off stump, he gets right behind the line and defends back to Nel
full outside off stump, and he clobbers it powerfully past mid-on to get the crowd buzzing
good length on off stump, pushed down to long-off
good length outside off stump, he gets a good look at it and then leaves it be
back of a length outside off stump, chopped to point
back of a length again, he pushes to point again
full on off stump, he nearly falls over as he works it to short midwicket

cleaned em up! It was full, no room to hit, and Oram swings across the line only to hear the death rattle behind him! What a celebration from Nel as he savours the sight of splayed stumps in front of him!

there it is, McCullum's not wasting time! Full outside off stump, he uses the feet well, and smashes that through the covers and just sets off for the pavilion, cool as a cucumber! New Zealand have made the semi-finals!
